.TH KBD-AUTO-LAYOUTD 1 "April 2026" "kbd-auto-layout 0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kbd-auto-layoutd \- automatic keyboard layout switching daemon for X11
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kbd-auto-layoutd
.RI [ --verbose ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kbd-auto-layoutd
is the background daemon for
.BR kbd-auto-layout .

It monitors detected keyboard devices in an X11 session and applies the first matching
configured rule. If no configured rule matches, it applies the configured default layout.

The daemon is typically run as a user systemd service.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --verbose
Enable more verbose logging.
.SH BEHAVIOR
The daemon:
.IP \(bu 2
loads configuration from the system and user config files
.IP \(bu 2
checks detected keyboards periodically
.IP \(bu 2
applies the first matching rule in configuration order
.IP \(bu 2
falls back to the default layout if no rule matches
.IP \(bu 2
reloads configuration on SIGHUP
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/kbd-auto-layout/config.ini
User configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/kbd-auto-layout/config.ini
System-wide configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/user/kbd-auto-layout.service
Installed user systemd unit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run manually:
.B kbd-auto-layoutd --verbose
.TP
Start as a user service:
.B systemctl --user enable --now kbd-auto-layout.service
.TP
Reload configuration:
.B systemctl --user kill -s HUP kbd-auto-layout.service
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kbd-auto-layoutctl (1),
.BR setxkbmap (1),
.BR xinput (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Giovanni Guarino
